A settlement committee consists of the following persons appointed by the relevant regional councilor for the constituency in which the settlement area is situated:
* the chief control officer of the settlement who is the chairperson of the settlement committee;
* representatives of governmental institutions at settlement area level including teachers, nurses, the Namibian police force, agriculture and other extension staff;
* representatives of non-governmental organisations operating in the settlement area;
* traditional leaders ;
* representatives of faith based organisations in the settlement area; and
* local representatives of development partners in the settlement area.
* participate in disaster risk assessment, disaster risk reduction activities and in disaster response;
* serve as an information source and reporting channel for the community with regard to disaster risk management matters;
* sensitise the community to the importance of understanding and heeding early warnings, the effects of disasters and appropriate responses;
* establish a disaster risk management task force;
* develop a settlement disaster contingency plan including early warning system and activation of emergency response;
* establish settlement emergency teams that respond to emergencies and disasters; and
* promote the recruitment, training and participation of volunteers in disaster management in the settlement area.

