An authorised officer may, during a state of national disaster, in the exercise of his or her powers or the performance of his or her functions or duties in terms of the provisions of this Act –
* enter, or break into and enter any premises;
* damage, destroy, pull down or remove any property; or
* preservation of the life of persons or animals;
* prevention of injury to persons or animals;
* removal of injured persons or animals;
* protection of property;
* prevention of damage to the environment; or
* combating of the state of disaster.
* take possession of or control over any land or other property for the purpose of dealing with the situation; or
* direct any person who is the owner of or who has possession of or control over any land or other property which is required for the purposes of dealing with the disaster situation to surrender the use of such land to a specified person or to a specified authority or to deliver or make available such property to a specified person in the service of that authority.

