The Fund consists of -
* moneys appropriated by Parliament for purposes of the Fund;
* donations or contributions made to the Fund for the purpose of the achievement of its objectives;
* moneys accruing to and vesting in the Fund from any other source and which accrues to the Fund;
* interest and dividends derived from the investment of moneys made on behalf of the Fund;
* advances made to the Fund in terms of section 47;
* any penalty or fine payable in terms of section 4(6), 7(3), 14(7), 56(2) or 57(3); and
* monies received from partnerships with stakeholders and development partners.

(1)	 Without derogation from the generality of section 48, the Fund may be applied to –
* research, capacity building and training programmes to promote and strengthen disaster risk management;
* the acquisition of land, equipment, materials and other assets and the construction of buildings in order to promote the objectives of this Act;
* meeting any expenses arising from the establishment and maintenance of the Fund;
* the acquisition of relief assistance, disaster recovery and rehabilitation assistance which may be made available to governmental institutions, regional councils or local authority councils which meet the prescribed requirements; and
* any other purpose which the Prime Minister considers to be in the interests of and contributes to the promotion of disaster risk management in Namibia.
* any banking institution or building society registered under the laws governing banking institutions and building societies in Namibia; or
* the Post Office Savings Bank established in terms of the Posts and Telecommunications Act, 1992 (Act No.19 of 1992).

An entity or person referred to in subsection (1) is subject to and
* respect the sovereignty of Namibia;
* obey local laws;
* cooperate with authorities;
